    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/asp.80.e90570.figure25>
    dc:description "Figure 25. Feaella (Tetrafeaella) cf. mucronata (Tullgren, 1907), scanning electron micrographs. Specimen used for imaging: F. cf. mucronata female paratype (ZMH-A 0010793). A carapace, dorsal view; B sternum ventral overview; C coxal spines in detail (highlighted in red). Scale bars: 0.2 mm (A, B); 0.1 mm (C)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/782017" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/asp.80.e90570.figure27>
    dc:description "Figure 27. Drawings of Feaella (Tetrafeaella) cf. mucronata (Tullgren, 1907): A carapace from dorsal; B leg IV; C left chela from dorsal with trichobothrial pattern; D right pedipalp from dorsal. Scale bars: 0.2 mm (A - C); 0.4 mm (D)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/782019" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/asp.80.e90570.figure5>
    dc:description "Figure 5. Antsirananaella gen. nov., scanning electron micrographs. Specimen used for imaging: A. leniae sp. nov. male paratype (ZMH-A 0016685). A carapace, dorsal; B sternum, ventral; C coxal spines (highlighted in red). Scale bars: 0.2 mm (A, B); 0.1 mm (C)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/781996" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/asp.80.e90570.figure7>
    dc:description "Figure 7. Drawings of Antsirananaella lorenzorum sp. nov.. A carapace, dorsal; B leg IV; C left chela from dorsal with trichobothrial pattern; D right pedipalp from dorsal. Scale bars: 0.2 mm (A - C); 0.4 mm (D)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/781998" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/asp.80.e90570.figure8>
    dc:description "Figure 8. Drawings of Antsirananaella faulstichi sp. nov.. A carapace, dorsal; B leg IV; C left chela from dorsal with trichobothrial pattern; D right pedipalp from dorsal. Scale bars: 0.2 mm (A - C); 0.4 mm (D)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/782000" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/asp.80.e90570.figure9>
    dc:description "Figure 9. Drawings of Antsirananaella leniae sp. nov.. A carapace dorsal; B leg IV; C left chela from dorsal with trichobothrial pattern; D right pedipalp from dorsal. Scale bars: 0.2 mm (A - C); 0.4 mm (D)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/782001" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/asp.80.e90570.figure10>
    dc:description "Figure 10. Drawings of Antsirananaella marlae sp. nov.: A carapace dorsal; B leg IV; C left chela from dorsal with trichobothrial pattern; D right pedipalp from dorsal. Scale bars: 0.2 mm (A - C); 0.4 mm (D)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/782002" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/asp.80.e90570.figure4>
    dc:description "Figure 4. Antsirananaella, gen. nov., habitus. Specimen used for imaging: A. leniae sp. nov. holotype (CAS 9072445). A dorsal; B ventral; C lateral. Scale bar: 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/781995" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/asp.80.e90570.figure6>
    dc:description "Figure 6. Antsirananaella, gen. nov., scanning electron micrographs. Specimen used for imaging: A. faulstichi sp. nov. allotype (ZMH-A 0016680). A right chela from ventral with specialized setae in a row in detail; B left chela with double trichobothrium dt in detail; C left chela from medial with terminal teeth in a compact group in detail. Scale bar: 0.2 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/781997" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

